  "prompt": "How are sandstones used?",
  "response": "Sandstones are used in a variety of ways, thanks to their durability, availability, and aesthetic qualities. Some common uses include:\n\n1. **Construction and Building Materials**: \n   - **Building facades and walls**: Sandstone is often used as a decorative and practical feature for exterior walls.\n   - **Flooring**: Because of its durability and natural beauty, sandstone is used for both indoor and outdoor flooring.\n   - **Interior decoration**: Sandstone's varied colors and textures can be used for indoor applications such as countertops, fireplace surrounds, and decorative accents.\n\n2. **Paving**: Sandstone is popular for paving walkways, patios, driveways, and other outdoor spaces due to its weather resistance and rustic appearance.\n\n3. **Architectural Elements**: Sandstone is used to carve statues, pillars, fountains, and other decorative architectural elements.\n\n4. **Landscaping**: Sandstone's natural look makes it suitable for garden walls, benches, steps, and other landscaping projects.\n\n5. **Industrial uses**: Sandstone can be crushed and used as an aggregate for concrete and road base.\n\n6. **Historical and Traditional Uses**: Many ancient temples, monuments, and buildings were crafted from sandstone due to its workability and durability.\n\n7. **Filtration Systems**: In some cases, crushed sandstone is used in water filtration systems as a natural filter.\n\n8. **Oil and Gas Reservoirs**: Some types of sandstone serve as reservoirs for petroleum and natural gas due to their porosity.\n\nBy leveraging these properties, sandstone continues to be an important material in various industries and applications.",
